history.content:
Normally CS 160 is taught using Andriod Studio, so that is the assumption I will work with right now

One time in the Summer they used Web Dev though

You only need to know how to write in Java for CS 160

Understanding the Data Structures that exist in the Java Library is very useful when data processing for the front end

You will NEED these things to not struggle hard in this class:

  • Reading and Writing ability (lots of articles and case study analysis)
  • Reading Documentation or Looking at Android Studio example videos
  • Java (assuming Android Studio), since they won't teach you that)
  • Basic art skills (some individual projects)
  • Understanding of the how and what Data Structures on a surface level (for data processing, but naive versions are okay as well)
    • I personally prefer that if it's made for me, might as well use it (as easy as calling a function)
  • Object-Oriented Programming
    • Java and Android development for each screen is based around that
    • I promise you it will make your code infinitely much cleaner and easier to wrap your head around if you use OOP (but they don't care about code quality, just the front end quality, but that's no good if your code isn't working)

The less of the above you have, the harder your time in CS 160 will be (for example, my reading skills and art skills is a bit whack, so I had to take some extra time for those)

The only thing as well to be aware of is when you have a project team. Some people I know aren't as fortunate to have a good team. Be ready to take the helm of your team at any time!
